description.p:
The biocompatible oily fluid according to the invention advantageously has one or another of the following characteristics, alone or in combination, or even all the following characteristics:
the oily ferrofluid is free of water and/or free of surfactant;
the phospholipid molecules ensure a coverage of 19 to 76%, preferably of 29 to 76% and preferentially of 34 to 50%, of the surface of the iron-oxide based magnetic nanoparticles;
the surface density of functionalization (also called surface density of grafting) in phospholipid molecules belongs to the range from 0.32 molecule/nm2 to 1.22 molecules/nm2, preferably from 0.48 molecule/nm2 to 1.22 molecules/nm2; and preferentially from 0.56 molecule/nm2 to 0.79 molecule/nm2;
the phospholipid(s) contain at least one fatty chain, preferably 2 fatty chains, in particular C6-C30 and preferably C8-C24 or even C10-C22, and in particular C18 saturated or mono- or polyunsaturated, branched or, preferably, linear hydrocarbon chains;
the oil phase comprises at least 70% by mass of fatty acid ester(s), preferably the oil phase comprises from 80% to 95% by mass of fatty acid ester(s), relative to the total mass of the oil phase;
the fatty acid ester(s) of the oil phase are chosen from C6-C12, preferably C6-C10, saturated fatty acid triglycerides and C6-C12, preferably C6-C10 saturated fatty acid propylene glycols used singly or in mixture;
the content of magnetic nanoparticles belongs to the range from 0.01% to 50% by mass, preferably from 0.1% to 10% by mass, relative to the total mass of the oily ferrofluid; when it is a question of magnetic nanoparticle content, this only comprises iron oxide-based magnetic nanoparticles and does not include functionalization;
the magnetic nanoparticles are in the form of a spheroid, a polyhedron such as nanocubes, bipyramids or nanostars, a wafer, a nanorod, a nanodisk, or a nanoflower;
the phospholipid(s) have an —O(O)P(OH)O− polar head and are preferably chosen from salts of 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphatidic acid and 1,2-distearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphatidic acid;
the biocompatible oily ferrofluid further comprises a lipophilic active ingredient, in particular chosen from cancer treatment drugs, such as paclitaxel, docetaxel, or carmustine.
